About Me.

My name is Nicole Sutedja, and I am a second-year Computer Science student at UC San Diego with a 3.925 GPA. I'm passionate about AI research, web development, and creating accessible technology education.

I believe technology should empower communities and bridge gaps. Whether I'm integrating AI platforms, building student marketplaces, or leading workshops for underrepresented students, I'm driven by the goal of making tech more inclusive and impactful.

First Steps.

I discovered my passion for computer science through its unique blend of creativity and problem-solving. What started as curiosity about algorithms quickly evolved into a dedication to using technology as a tool for social good.

Through my coursework in Data Structures, Algorithms, and System Programming, combined with hands-on experience in AI research and web development, I've developed a foundation that allows me to tackle complex challenges while staying focused on user impact.

My Experience.

I've worked across AI research, product management, and web development in both academic and startup environments. At Sciencia Consulting, I integrated APIs from five AI platforms and contributed to workshops teaching practical AI use to graduate students.

Currently, I'm leading the development of Low-Price Center, a student-centered marketplace at UCSD, while conducting research on specifications-based grading frameworks under Prof. Mia Minnes. I've also built full-stack web applications using React, TypeScript, and SQL.

Beyond technical work, I'm deeply committed to community leadership. As Head of Events for San Diego Indonesian Association and CSE Curriculum Director for CS foreach, I've organized events for over 140 students and led workshops that bring computer science education to K-12 students in underrepresented communities.

Tech Stack.

Languages

Python, Java, JavaScript, TypeScript, HTML, CSS, C

Frameworks & Tools

React, SQL, Git, Neon, Microsoft Office, Canva

Skills

Web Development, AI Integration, API Development, Database Management
